-- Indian shares rise after 2 days of falls; Bharti Airtel surges 5.5 pct
-- By Indulal PM
-- Wed Jul 30, 2014 06:10AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, July 30 (Reuters) - Indian shares ended higher on Wednesday, snapping two days of falls on gains in blue-chips such as Bharti Airtel <BRTI.NS>, Lupin <LUPN.NS> and Dr Reddy's Laboratories <REDY.NS> after their earnings beat estimates.

The broader NSE index <.NSEI> provisionally closed 0.55 percent higher at 7,791.40, while the benchmark BSE index <.BSESN> gained 0.37 percent to 26,087.42.